#!/bin/bash
# dotfiles-rollback — Restaura dotfiles desde el último snapshot local
# No requiere git ni internet — funciona con el backup local
# Uso: dotfiles-rollback [--list] [--snapshot YYYY-MM-DD_HH-MM-SS]

set -uo pipefail

BACKUP_DIR="$HOME/.cache/black-ice/backups"

RED='\033[0;31m'; GREEN='\033[0;32m'; YELLOW='\033[1;33m'
CYAN='\033[0;36m'; BOLD='\033[1m'; NC='\033[0m'

info()    { echo -e "${CYAN}[INFO]${NC} $*"; }
success() { echo -e "${GREEN}[OK]${NC}   $*"; }
warn()    { echo -e "${YELLOW}[WARN]${NC} $*"; }
error()   { echo -e "${RED}[ERR]${NC}  $*" >&2; exit 1; }

LIST_ONLY=false
TARGET_SNAPSHOT=""

for arg in "$@"; do
    case $arg in
        --list) LIST_ONLY=true ;;
        --snapshot) TARGET_SNAPSHOT="${2:-}"; shift ;;
    esac
done

echo -e "\n${BOLD}${CYAN}BLACK-ICE ARCH — Dotfiles Rollback${NC}\n"

if [[ ! -d "$BACKUP_DIR" ]]; then
    error "No hay backups en $BACKUP_DIR. Ejecuta dotfiles-update primero."
fi

# Listar snapshots disponibles
SNAPSHOTS=( $(ls -dt "$BACKUP_DIR"/20* 2>/dev/null) )
if [[ ${#SNAPSHOTS[@]} -eq 0 ]]; then
    error "No se encontraron snapshots en $BACKUP_DIR"
fi

if [[ "$LIST_ONLY" == true ]]; then
    echo -e "Snapshots disponibles:\n"
    for i in "${!SNAPSHOTS[@]}"; do
        label=$(basename "${SNAPSHOTS[$i]}")
        size=$(du -sh "${SNAPSHOTS[$i]}" 2>/dev/null | cut -f1)
        [[ $i -eq 0 ]] && mark="${GREEN}← más reciente${NC}" || mark=""
        echo -e "  ${CYAN}[$((i+1))]${NC} $label  (${size})  $mark"
    done
    echo ""
    exit 0
fi

# Seleccionar snapshot
if [[ -n "$TARGET_SNAPSHOT" ]]; then
    SNAPSHOT="$BACKUP_DIR/$TARGET_SNAPSHOT"
    [[ ! -d "$SNAPSHOT" ]] && error "Snapshot no encontrado: $TARGET_SNAPSHOT"
else
    # Usar el más reciente por defecto
    SNAPSHOT="${SNAPSHOTS[0]}"
    LABEL=$(basename "$SNAPSHOT")

    echo -e "Snapshots disponibles:\n"
    for i in "${!SNAPSHOTS[@]}"; do
        label=$(basename "${SNAPSHOTS[$i]}")
        [[ $i -eq 0 ]] && mark=" ${GREEN}← más reciente${NC}" || mark=""
        echo -e "  ${CYAN}[$((i+1))]${NC} $label$mark"
    done

    echo ""
    read -p "¿Qué snapshot restaurar? [1-${#SNAPSHOTS[@]}, Enter=más reciente]: " choice < /dev/tty
    choice="${choice:-1}"

    if [[ "$choice" =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]] && (( choice >= 1 && choice <= ${#SNAPSHOTS[@]} )); then
        SNAPSHOT="${SNAPSHOTS[$((choice-1))]}"
    else
        error "Selección inválida"
    fi
fi

LABEL=$(basename "$SNAPSHOT")
warn "Se restaurará el snapshot: $LABEL"
read -p "¿Confirmar? [s/N]: " confirm < /dev/tty
[[ "${confirm,,}" != "s" ]] && { warn "Cancelado."; exit 0; }

# --- RESTAURAR ---
info "Restaurando desde $LABEL ..."

for dir in hypr waybar kitty wofi swaync wlogout fastfetch nftables; do
    src="$SNAPSHOT/$dir"
    dst="$HOME/.config/$dir"
    if [[ -d "$src" ]]; then
        # Quitar symlink actual si existe
        [[ -L "$dst" ]] && unlink "$dst"
        [[ -d "$dst" ]] && rm -rf "$dst"
        cp -r "$src" "$dst"
        success "$dir restaurado"
    fi
done

if [[ -f "$SNAPSHOT/.zshrc" ]]; then
    cp "$SNAPSHOT/.zshrc" "$HOME/.zshrc"
    success ".zshrc restaurado"
fi

# Recargar servicios
info "Recargando servicios..."
pgrep -x waybar &>/dev/null && pkill -SIGUSR2 waybar 2>/dev/null && success "Waybar recargado" || true
[[ -n "${HYPRLAND_INSTANCE_SIGNATURE:-}" ]] && hyprctl reload &>/dev/null && success "Hyprland recargado" || true
pgrep -x swaync &>/dev/null && swaync-client --reload-config &>/dev/null && success "SwayNC recargado" || true

echo -e "\n${GREEN}${BOLD}✓ Rollback completo desde $LABEL${NC}"
